@santoshconflux Why do you need a call or demo? Will pulling this code in and testing the feature on your environment not validate if the issue has been solved? 
Also if there needs to be a demo, does it mean a UI is needed because that will mean we accepting this PR only if there is a UI for it already given Fineract does not have a UI. Do you want him to show you a postman call to an endpoint so you see the response. It looks like the issue is not well understood. 
If that is the case, then we need to create a confluence page or this or update the JIRA ticket and even discuss on the mailing list. I think we can merge this code and do the UI tests and confluence pages later given @angelboxes has been so patient with us.

@awasum , We know @angelboxes did great job including this feature.   Since  UI is not yet developed in Community app level and we still have open ticket https://github.com/openMF/community-app/issues/2997  which GSOC student can work upon. 
All we can check it with Postman only. 
@angelboxes can walk me through Postman or share some use cases. We had demo long time back and in order to just refresh our memory I asked for quick demo , not detailed one, so that I can figure out whether it could create any regressions. 
We should not forget that loan 'product' is very base of whole loan module and any new inclusions in the loan product demands to test whole or at least to some extent of loan module thoroughly for regressions.

@vishwasbabu those replies were very helpful and clearly establishes the need for either a demo or for @santoshconflux to merge the UI code and manually test the functionality from his end:

@angelboxes 
The purpose of the demo is to demonstrate end to end the rates module work you've done since we don't have full integration test coverage in place. Santosh wanted to see a demo or manually test the code via the UI locally to ensure no regressions were introduced.
